2
00:00:21.121 --> 00:00:23.386
Excuse me. you're in my seat.

3
00:00:24.124 --> 00:00:26.616
Am I? Actually. yes. you are.

4
00:00:26.693 --> 00:00:28.628
You one of those
weirdo compulsives

5
00:00:28.695 --> 00:00:30.573
who come to the same
restaurant. sit in the same chair.

6
00:00:30.597 --> 00:00:32.896
and eat the same food every day?

7
00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:36.035
No. no. no. I was sitting
right there three minutes ago.

8
00:00:36.103 --> 00:00:39.403
and then I went outside
to get myself a paper.

9
00:00:39.473 --> 00:00:43.308
I ordered a juice. and look. I made a
crawling snake with the straw wrapper.

10
00:00:43.377 --> 00:00:45.121
You can finish it if you
think you're up to the job.

11
00:00:45.145 --> 00:00:47.137
I'm sorry. You want me to move?

12
00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:48.648
Not anymore.

13
00:00:49.950 --> 00:00:51.550
So. what's up? I
don't have time to talk.

14
00:00:51.585 --> 00:00:52.929
But you haven't heard
what I'm going to say.

15
00:00:52.953 --> 00:00:55.855
See. now we've already
talked more than I wanted to.

16
00:01:03.497 --> 00:01:05.295
Well. I did give you
my seat. you know.

17
00:01:05.365 --> 00:01:06.609
I think that gets
me one question.

18
00:01:06.633 --> 00:01:08.397
Listen. diner guy... Shawn.

19
00:01:08.468 --> 00:01:10.130
Shawn. Flattered. really.

20
00:01:10.203 --> 00:01:12.035
Very often. I am happy
to meet new people.

21
00:01:12.105 --> 00:01:14.438
But today. right here.
right now. I can't talk.

22
00:01:14.508 --> 00:01:16.238
I understand. I do.

23
00:01:16.643 --> 00:01:18.839
What if I do the
talking for both of us?

24
00:01:18.912 --> 00:01:20.005
Have at it!

25
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:21.291
Do you mind if I read the paper

26
00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:23.546
and stare aimlessly out the
window while you two talk?

27
00:01:23.617 --> 00:01:26.109
No. Can I get a
name to work with?

28
00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:28.015
Juliet.

29
00:01:28.689 --> 00:01:30.885
Well. it's very nice
to meet you. Juliet.

30
00:01:30.958 --> 00:01:32.769
(IN WOMAN'S VOICE) It's
nice to meet you. too. Shawn.

31
00:01:32.793 --> 00:01:36.389
And I am sorry about your
seat. So. lunch is on me.

32
00:01:36.463 --> 00:01:37.897
So. what do you do for a living?

33
00:01:37.965 --> 00:01:39.242
(IN HIS OWN VOICE) I
do a little bit of everything.

34
00:01:39.266 --> 00:01:40.577
(IN WOMAN'S VOICE)
Oh. that sounds interesting.

35
00:01:40.601 --> 00:01:42.092
And maybe a
little bit dangerous.

36
00:01:42.169 --> 00:01:43.513
Oh. I like your
jacket. I like it...

37
00:01:43.537 --> 00:01:45.506
Okay. can I stop you here?

38
00:01:45.572 --> 00:01:47.734
First off. in your
portrayal of me.

39
00:01:47.808 --> 00:01:49.367
I sound like I'm in
the eighth grade.

40
00:01:49.443 --> 00:01:51.821
Well. in my portrayal of you. you
only have an eighth grade education.

41
00:01:51.845 --> 00:01:53.074
(SCOFFS)

42
00:01:53.981 --> 00:01:57.782
All right. smarten
you up. College. yeah?

43
00:01:57.851 --> 00:02:00.980
Top your class.
graduate early... Got it.

44
00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:04.682
(IN WOMAN'S VOICE) I'm new to
town. and I don't know many people.

45
00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:09.223
But I do know my
cats. Two of them.

46
00:02:09.630 --> 00:02:11.064
The gray one is
very affectionate.

47
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:14.431
the white one makes me work
much. much harder for the attention.

48
00:02:14.501 --> 00:02:15.992
And what about your family?

49
00:02:17.571 --> 00:02:19.403
My family is amazing!

50
00:02:20.007 --> 00:02:23.068
My parents have been together
for. what is it. 30 years now?

51
00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:24.668
Okay. do we know each other?

52
00:02:24.745 --> 00:02:27.408
Yes. you were the
girl who stole my seat!

53
00:02:38.058 --> 00:02:39.993
Oh. my gosh. you're a cop!

54
00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:41.060
I'm not a cop!

55
00:02:41.128 --> 00:02:44.098
The paper. the vantage
point. the layout. of course!

56
00:02:44.164 --> 00:02:48.158
You got defensive when Scary
Guy walked in. you're totally a cop!

57
00:02:48.235 --> 00:02:51.171
Okay. Shawn. I may
need you to do me a favor.

58
00:02:51.238 --> 00:02:52.729
Name it. Duck!

59
00:02:53.073 --> 00:02:54.234
OFFICER: Police!

60
00:02:55.242 --> 00:02:56.437
Gun! Go!

61
00:02:58.111 --> 00:02:59.704
Let me go! Get him up!

62
00:03:00.414 --> 00:03:01.746
Come on!

63
00:03:15.495 --> 00:03:17.623
First time pulling your gun?

64
00:03:18.532 --> 00:03:19.727
Maybe.

65
00:03:33.814 --> 00:03:37.410
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

66
00:03:37.484 --> 00:03:40.579
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

67
00:03:40.654 --> 00:03:43.852
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

68
00:03:43.924 --> 00:03:48.055
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

69
00:03:54.334 --> 00:03:56.530
Thirty seconds. Mr. Guster.

70
00:03:58.371 --> 00:04:01.967
A-G...

71
00:04:05.378 --> 00:04:06.607
G...

72
00:04:13.887 --> 00:04:16.914
Let me start over!
"Aggiornamento."

73
00:04:18.125 --> 00:04:19.252
A...

74
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:22.422
G...

75
00:04:23.497 --> 00:04:24.760
G...

76
00:04:34.407 --> 00:04:35.500
O...

77
00:04:35.575 --> 00:04:36.599
(BUZZER RINGS)

78
00:04:36.676 --> 00:04:38.144
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

79
00:04:42.682 --> 00:04:44.327
<i>MAN ON TV: Beautiful
Santa Barbara. California.</i>

80
00:04:44.351 --> 00:04:47.844
<i>is the backdrop for this afternoon's
coverage of the American Spelling Bee.</i>

81
00:04:47.921 --> 00:04:50.186
<i>being held at the
downtown Cabrillo Theater.</i>

82
00:04:50.257 --> 00:04:52.453
<i>Champions from all over
these western United States</i>

83
00:04:52.526 --> 00:04:54.688
<i>have made the trek to test...</i>

84
00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:57.829
What are you watching? Nothing.

85
00:04:57.898 --> 00:05:00.493
Is that Korean
porn? Come on. man!

86
00:05:00.567 --> 00:05:03.833
It's the Regional Finals of
the American Spelling Bee.

87
00:05:03.904 --> 00:05:04.963
What?

88
00:05:05.438 --> 00:05:07.805
Don't mock me.
It's a huge event.

89
00:05:08.241 --> 00:05:12.042
No. I'm just... I'm shocked that
you didn't take the whole day off.

90
00:05:12.112 --> 00:05:14.240
It's on Sports Cal Two.
for your information.

91
00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:15.491
And it's hosted by Bud Collins.

92
00:05:15.515 --> 00:05:18.781
Really? Did they bump the car
washing championships for this?

93
00:05:18.852 --> 00:05:22.380
And is it over soon? 'Cause I'd like
to get back to the woodcarving finals.

94
00:05:22.455 --> 00:05:24.433
<i>MAN ON TV: Let's recap this
morning's unexpected high drama.</i>

95
00:05:24.457 --> 00:05:26.289
It's being held in
Santa Barbara this year.

96
00:05:26.359 --> 00:05:29.420
Down at the Cabrillo.
It's huge. Sold out.

97
00:05:29.696 --> 00:05:30.840
<i>All the experts are
shaking their heads.</i>

98
00:05:30.864 --> 00:05:32.575
I tried to get tickets. but
you gotta know somebody.

99
00:05:32.599 --> 00:05:35.194
Somebody lame. Dude. I can't
believe you're watching that!

100
00:05:35.268 --> 00:05:37.567
I'm taping it! And I don't
care what you think. Shawn.

101
00:05:37.637 --> 00:05:38.917
I watch the bee
semis every year.

102
00:05:38.972 --> 00:05:41.884
Okay. for your sake and mine. stop giving
the spelling bee hip little nicknames.

103
00:05:41.908 --> 00:05:44.571
(SHUSHING) <i>COLLINS: For
those of you who have just joined us.</i>

104
00:05:44.644 --> 00:05:48.308
<i>well. a bit of a shock.
And a little sad. too.</i>

105
00:05:48.849 --> 00:05:53.082
<i>The heavy favorite has had a
bad spell. and Brendan Vu is out!</i>

106
00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:55.118
What? <i>Boo-hoo for Vu. Bud.</i>

107
00:05:55.188 --> 00:05:57.714
No way. Brendan
Vu is out? Already?

108
00:05:57.791 --> 00:05:58.868
Okay. now you're
just scaring me.

109
00:05:58.892 --> 00:06:01.037
Come on. Shawn. He took second
last year. everybody knows that!

110
00:06:01.061 --> 00:06:05.157
No. Gus. nobody knows that.
except for Brendan and his mother.

111
00:06:05.232 --> 00:06:06.393
Okay.

112
00:06:06.466 --> 00:06:08.264
<i>We're gonna show this again.</i>

113
00:06:08.335 --> 00:06:10.531
<i>It looks like young Mr. Vu</i>

114
00:06:10.604 --> 00:06:12.004
<i>may be having trouble breathing.</i>

115
00:06:12.072 --> 00:06:14.769
<i>He does look to be under
some sort of duress. Bud.</i>

116
00:06:14.841 --> 00:06:17.436
<i>His inhaler did not appear
to help. and Vu tumbled.</i>

117
00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:18.603
<i>(AUDIENCE GASPS)</i>

118
00:06:18.678 --> 00:06:19.722
Dang! <i>Paramedics
rushed to the scene.</i>

119
00:06:19.746 --> 00:06:21.757
<i>and within moments. the competition
had taken an unexpected turn.</i>

120
00:06:21.781 --> 00:06:24.046
Wait a second. Did you see that?

121
00:06:29.856 --> 00:06:32.416
This is no accident. There's
something wrong with that inhaler.

122
00:06:32.492 --> 00:06:34.358
Shawn. get out of here.

123
00:06:34.461 --> 00:06:37.625
(PHONE RINGS) <i>For 35 minutes.
competition was suspended.</i>

124
00:06:37.697 --> 00:06:38.697
Psych.

125
00:06:38.765 --> 00:06:42.429
<i>And Vu and his family were
rushed to the hospital.</i> It's the Chief.

126
00:06:42.502 --> 00:06:44.027
I'll have to check with Gus.

127
00:06:44.104 --> 00:06:45.732
Are we available?

128
00:06:45.972 --> 00:06:47.497
Appears we are.

129
00:06:47.574 --> 00:06:48.803
We'll be right there.

130
00:06:49.542 --> 00:06:50.887
What? I can get us
into the spelling bee.

131
00:06:50.911 --> 00:06:51.935
Really?

132
00:06:52.012 --> 00:06:53.723
Guess I was right about the
whole Bandon Dunes thing.

133
00:06:53.747 --> 00:06:55.340
Brendan Vu. Sure.

134
00:06:55.415 --> 00:06:56.659
They need a psychic
detective for that?

135
00:06:56.683 --> 00:06:58.083
They don't.

136
00:06:58.919 --> 00:07:00.751
unless he was sabotaged.

137
00:07:01.488 --> 00:07:03.753
The kid said his
inhaler felt funny.

138
00:07:03.823 --> 00:07:06.122
When he used it. his hand stung.

139
00:07:06.626 --> 00:07:08.492
paramedics get there.
there's no inhaler.

140
00:07:08.561 --> 00:07:10.826
Apparently. the thing
just vanished into thin air.

141
00:07:10.897 --> 00:07:13.162
Shawn. we are so
taking this! Let's go!

142
00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:16.697
How come I can't get you this
excited about girls? Let's go. Shawn!

143
00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:18.033
Or Mexico?

144
00:07:26.646 --> 00:07:27.670
We're here!

145
00:07:27.747 --> 00:07:30.376
Go on in. Mr. Spencer. I've
arranged everything you need inside.

146
00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:33.045
You're leaving? Oh. I was only
here for the mayor's presentation.

147
00:07:33.119 --> 00:07:35.054
and we have a robbery
standoff across town.

148
00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:36.817
Whoa. shouldn't I
go to the hospital.

149
00:07:36.890 --> 00:07:38.825
meet the victim.
get his statement?

150
00:07:38.892 --> 00:07:41.191
Mr. Spencer. the
case is sabotage.

151
00:07:41.361 --> 00:07:44.991
There are 43 remaining contestants.
all presumably with a motive.

152
00:07:45.065 --> 00:07:48.126
Now. you can read guilt just
by talking with someone. right?

153
00:07:48.201 --> 00:07:49.294
Do it.

154
00:07:49.369 --> 00:07:51.489
You want us to talk to all
of them? And their parents.

155
00:07:51.538 --> 00:07:53.598
Today? Mmm-hmm. By 5:00.

156
00:07:53.673 --> 00:07:55.471
In two days. this
whole thing is over.

157
00:07:55.542 --> 00:07:57.787
At that time. all the witnesses
will be in 100 different cities

158
00:07:57.811 --> 00:07:59.279
all over the western
United States.

159
00:07:59.346 --> 00:08:01.815
So. it's now or never.

160
00:08:03.516 --> 00:08:04.575
Good luck.

161
00:08:08.088 --> 00:08:11.149
<i>COLLINS: Spellmaster Elvin
Cavanaugh is a secretive guy.</i>

162
00:08:11.224 --> 00:08:15.559
<i>and yet. he has called for a
press conference after this round!</i>

163
00:08:16.229 --> 00:08:18.255
<i>Can you repeat that. please?</i>

164
00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:19.822
<i>"Butyraceous."</i>

165
00:08:20.166 --> 00:08:21.930
<i>Definition. please?</i>

166
00:08:22.068 --> 00:08:23.400
<i>Adjective.</i>

167
00:08:23.536 --> 00:08:26.131
<i>"Having the
characteristics of butter."</i>

168
00:08:28.908 --> 00:08:30.399
This thing's been
sold out for weeks.

169
00:08:30.477 --> 00:08:34.175
I can see why. It moves so
fast. it's like hockey with words.

170
00:08:34.447 --> 00:08:36.780
There's Elvin Cavanaugh. the
greatest spell champion ever.

171
00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:39.342
He's been the
spellmaster for 14 years.

172
00:08:39.419 --> 00:08:40.648
He's a legend. Wow.

173
00:08:40.720 --> 00:08:42.211
<i>"Butyraceous."</i>

174
00:08:42.555 --> 00:08:44.854
He sits up there all by
himself in that fancy box?

175
00:08:44.924 --> 00:08:46.222
<i>Language of origin?</i>

176
00:08:46.292 --> 00:08:47.603
What is he. the
Phantom of the Opera?

177
00:08:47.627 --> 00:08:50.529
He's a huge celebrity! He
can't just sit in the crowd!

178
00:08:50.597 --> 00:08:52.031
<i>Can you repeat the word?</i>

179
00:08:52.098 --> 00:08:53.726
<i>"Butyraceous."</i>

180
00:08:55.101 --> 00:08:56.379
<i>"Butyraceous"?</i>
Oh. come on. dude.

181
00:08:56.403 --> 00:08:57.666
you're not bored at all?

182
00:08:57.737 --> 00:09:00.263
Do you know how to
spell any of these words?

183
00:09:00.340 --> 00:09:03.276
Proudly. I have never
heard of any of these words.

184
00:09:03.343 --> 00:09:05.175
I file these words
under "Things to say

185
00:09:05.245 --> 00:09:07.305
"when I want to be ridiculed
or kicked out of bed."

186
00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:10.612
See. the problem is that butyraceous
is clearly a Round One word.

187
00:09:10.683 --> 00:09:11.776
Oh. God. stop talking.

188
00:09:11.851 --> 00:09:13.996
I'd like to pretend we still
have things in common. Gus!

189
00:09:14.020 --> 00:09:17.286
Well. instead of sitting here.
maybe we should get to work!

190
00:09:22.762 --> 00:09:25.493
Try not to break anything.

191
00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:26.565
Wow!

192
00:09:27.434 --> 00:09:29.562
So this is what it looks like.

193
00:09:29.636 --> 00:09:30.636
What?

194
00:09:30.703 --> 00:09:32.171
The comfort room.

195
00:09:32.238 --> 00:09:34.332
This is where you go to
deal with missing a word.

196
00:09:34.407 --> 00:09:36.018
Oh. yeah? Where do
they take you to deal with

197
00:09:36.042 --> 00:09:37.908
missing your entire childhood?

198
00:09:37.977 --> 00:09:41.744
Shawn. this misplaced malevolence
you have with the spelling bee

199
00:09:41.815 --> 00:09:43.681
is getting monotonous.

200
00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:46.051
Stop hating on the bee!

201
00:09:46.619 --> 00:09:49.521
I'm sorry. ma'am. I do apologize
for his inappropriate virulence.

202
00:09:49.589 --> 00:09:51.801
Why are you using all these
big-ass words all of a sudden?

203
00:09:51.825 --> 00:09:53.555
I'm not doing that.

204
00:09:55.829 --> 00:09:57.593
That's preposterous!

205
00:09:57.964 --> 00:09:59.899
I was in the
spelling bee myself.

206
00:09:59.966 --> 00:10:00.966
I almost won.

207
00:10:01.034 --> 00:10:02.078
Dude. are you still on that?

208
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:04.537
Of course I'm still on
it! I know it wasn't "O"!

209
00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:07.870
You may have five minutes
with each contestant. no more.

210
00:10:07.941 --> 00:10:10.001
If the room is needed.
you'll be asked to vacate.

211
00:10:10.076 --> 00:10:12.341
I'll begin with the
eliminated contestants.

212
00:10:12.412 --> 00:10:14.223
Actually. we'd only like
to speak with the ones

213
00:10:14.247 --> 00:10:17.581
that were still in the competition
when the accident occurred.

214
00:10:17.650 --> 00:10:19.084
Ms. Foote.

215
00:10:20.286 --> 00:10:23.518
And let's start with the
shifty-eyed ones. shall we?

216
00:10:25.792 --> 00:10:28.193
And you were there
the whole time?

217
00:10:29.229 --> 00:10:30.424
I was.

218
00:10:31.131 --> 00:10:32.599
Assimilation.

219
00:10:33.399 --> 00:10:38.167
A-S-S-I-M-I-L-A-T-I-O-N.
Assimilation.

220
00:10:39.172 --> 00:10:42.506
My son. no one expect
him to come this far.

221
00:10:42.575 --> 00:10:46.342
But he surprise everyone.
You watch him win.

222
00:10:46.412 --> 00:10:49.314
Oh. I don't know. Are they
running odds on this thing now?

223
00:10:49.382 --> 00:10:51.442
'Cause I've got some
cash I'd like to lay down

224
00:10:51.518 --> 00:10:53.885
on the really. really tall girl
with the bulldog underbite.

225
00:10:53.953 --> 00:10:55.148
What. is she on stilts?

226
00:10:55.221 --> 00:10:56.416
(SHAWN LAUGHING)

227
00:10:56.489 --> 00:10:57.821
You do not understand.

228
00:10:57.891 --> 00:11:00.884
This contest. it is
money for scholarship.

229
00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:03.725
It is entry into any
school in the future.

230
00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:05.965
Yeah. Shawn.

231
00:11:06.032 --> 00:11:08.763
The winner of this competition
can just about choose his university.

232
00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:09.859
Your friend is right.

233
00:11:09.936 --> 00:11:12.405
And it teaches
grace under pressure.

234
00:11:12.472 --> 00:11:15.135
Poise. Dignity.

235
00:11:16.843 --> 00:11:19.642
All things you can get at a
hot-dog eating competition.

236
00:11:19.712 --> 00:11:20.907
Plus...

237
00:11:22.916 --> 00:11:23.916
Hot dogs.

238
00:11:24.717 --> 00:11:26.345
Still studying. huh?

239
00:11:26.419 --> 00:11:29.355
Oh. she loves it. Won't
put that thing down.

240
00:11:29.722 --> 00:11:32.021
Well. kudos on the childrearing.

241
00:11:32.425 --> 00:11:34.792
Let me know how
the therapy goes.

242
00:11:35.094 --> 00:11:36.094
Huh?

243
00:11:36.229 --> 00:11:40.667
We're gonna keep rolling because of the
exceptional request by Elvin Cavanaugh.

244
00:11:40.733 --> 00:11:44.101
a behind-the-scenes guy.
to give a press conference

245
00:11:44.237 --> 00:11:47.002
right here at this stage
of the competition!

246
00:11:47.073 --> 00:11:48.166
<i>What's that all about?</i>

247
00:11:48.241 --> 00:11:49.919
<i>Well. I mean. this could
be something big. Bud.</i>

248
00:11:49.943 --> 00:11:52.970
<i>I mean. this year's competition has
just been peppered with controversy.</i>

249
00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:54.241
<i>It certainly has.</i>

250
00:11:54.314 --> 00:11:58.684
<i>Well. he's been watching from a
private box on the balcony. but now.</i>

251
00:11:58.751 --> 00:12:01.346
he's going to come out
so that we can see him.

252
00:12:01.421 --> 00:12:03.913
(GRUNTS) This could
be something big. Bud.

253
00:12:03.990 --> 00:12:06.516
I think he's having
difficulty breathing!

254
00:12:06.593 --> 00:12:08.619
He does look under duress. Bud.

255
00:12:09.495 --> 00:12:11.464
(PEOPLE SCREAMING) Oh. jeez!

256
00:12:11.531 --> 00:12:13.625
Oh. my! Oh. my God! Oh!

257
00:12:13.700 --> 00:12:16.101
WOMAN: Call 911!
MAN: Okay. move over.

258
00:12:16.169 --> 00:12:18.695
(ALL CLAMORING)

259
00:12:20.206 --> 00:12:23.199
Okay. Not to
belittle this guy's life.

260
00:12:24.110 --> 00:12:26.807
but this just got more interesting
than the woodcarving finals.

261
00:12:32.385 --> 00:12:33.819
(ZIPPER CLOSES)

262
00:12:38.925 --> 00:12:41.326
When do we decide if we
should cancel this event?

263
00:12:41.394 --> 00:12:43.192
Why would we cancel?

264
00:12:43.296 --> 00:12:47.131
Well. a body did just
tumble into the crowd.

265
00:12:48.034 --> 00:12:49.366
Didn't land on anybody.

266
00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:50.596
It might be traumatic.

267
00:12:50.670 --> 00:12:51.694
For who?

268
00:12:51.771 --> 00:12:54.083
The mayor. when he realizes all
the hotel rooms are now empty?

269
00:12:54.107 --> 00:12:56.667
We could postpone at least
a day. I'm sure that's allowed.

270
00:12:56.743 --> 00:12:59.508
Do you have any idea how
important this event is to the city?

271
00:12:59.579 --> 00:13:01.946
Now. unhealthy
guy has heart attack.

272
00:13:02.015 --> 00:13:03.984
falls over railing. Case closed.

273
00:13:04.050 --> 00:13:06.144
Certainly not declaring
it a crime scene.

274
00:13:06.219 --> 00:13:08.711
Come on. you can
introduce me to the press.

275
00:13:08.921 --> 00:13:11.049
Okay. just be sensitive.

276
00:13:11.357 --> 00:13:13.758
How about if we don't sell
the seat the guy landed on?

277
00:13:16.729 --> 00:13:17.924
Can I help you?

278
00:13:17.997 --> 00:13:19.363
Has anyone come out of there?

279
00:13:19.432 --> 00:13:21.076
Just the cops. I've been
here the whole time.

280
00:13:21.100 --> 00:13:22.211
Did you hear
anything from in there?

281
00:13:22.235 --> 00:13:24.227
I'm sorry. who are you?

282
00:13:24.537 --> 00:13:27.405
I'm Shawn Spencer. I'm a
psychic with the police department.

283
00:13:28.007 --> 00:13:29.952
I'm sorry. Mr. Spencer.
Look. I don't doubt your ability.

284
00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:34.209
I actually have an aunt who can see
apparitions. and some spooky stuff.

285
00:13:34.681 --> 00:13:38.482
But they told me not to let anybody
in here without a badge. so...

286
00:13:38.551 --> 00:13:39.644
I see.

287
00:13:40.553 --> 00:13:42.579
Okay. As long as you feel safe.

288
00:13:43.022 --> 00:13:44.149
Safe?

289
00:13:45.291 --> 00:13:48.659
What with the dead guy's spirit
being here. and him being so angry.

290
00:13:50.663 --> 00:13:52.029
How angry?

291
00:13:53.032 --> 00:13:56.093
Well. considering he might
have just been murdered.

292
00:13:56.169 --> 00:13:58.035
that's definitely a negative.

293
00:13:58.104 --> 00:13:59.629
(SHAWN LAUGHING)

294
00:13:59.939 --> 00:14:00.998
Man. I wouldn't be happy!

295
00:14:01.074 --> 00:14:02.542
(ALL LAUGH)

296
00:14:05.111 --> 00:14:07.273
(SHRIEKING)

297
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:10.775
No. please. spare me!
I'm here to help you! Gus!

298
00:14:11.017 --> 00:14:14.181
Back me up here! Oh! Oh! Oh!

299
00:14:16.723 --> 00:14:18.214
Segrete ammunus!

300
00:14:18.291 --> 00:14:20.055
(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

301
00:14:26.466 --> 00:14:29.800
(STAMMERING) You guys just
take a quick little look-see. okay?

302
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:31.599
I'll be downstairs!

303
00:14:37.577 --> 00:14:39.068
Come on. get up!

304
00:14:39.278 --> 00:14:40.371
(GROANS)

305
00:14:52.558 --> 00:14:55.995
Well. we certainly
know what his vice was.

306
00:14:56.929 --> 00:14:58.261
He was a heavy eater. so what?

307
00:14:58.331 --> 00:15:01.665
Nothing. I'm just thinking
Lassiter's heart attack theory

308
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:03.498
might not be so far off.

309
00:15:08.708 --> 00:15:10.540
Who's Contestant 1953?

310
00:15:10.610 --> 00:15:12.772
It only goes up
to 200-something.

311
00:15:14.447 --> 00:15:15.938
What's 1953 mean?

312
00:15:16.816 --> 00:15:18.011
Nothing.

313
00:15:18.317 --> 00:15:21.583
Is it a rule? No. they don't
really number the rules like that.

314
00:15:29.228 --> 00:15:31.493
Think there was an altercation?

315
00:15:31.597 --> 00:15:33.930
No. something else. He
was all by himself up here.

316
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.559
You smell that?

317
00:15:36.169 --> 00:15:37.364
Dude. don't look at me.

318
00:15:37.437 --> 00:15:38.928
It's sulfuric.

319
00:15:39.472 --> 00:15:41.116
Gus. I am not the one
who had the egg salad.

320
00:15:41.140 --> 00:15:43.769
No. no. no. We manufactured
something last year. heavy stuff.

321
00:15:43.843 --> 00:15:45.675
When it starts to go
bad. smelled the same.

322
00:15:45.745 --> 00:15:48.340
You could pick out a
bottle across the warehouse.

323
00:15:49.248 --> 00:15:51.080
I can't smell anything!

324
00:15:51.150 --> 00:15:53.381
Well. you don't have
the supersmeller.

325
00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:56.787
Gus! You have got to stop
calling your nose the supersmeller.

326
00:15:56.989 --> 00:15:58.389
You wanna nickname a body part?

327
00:15:58.458 --> 00:16:00.017
Nickname your butt. man!

328
00:16:00.092 --> 00:16:02.857
Call it the "tightbouncer."
or the "hexagon."

329
00:16:02.929 --> 00:16:05.489
Ladies are gonna
dig that. I'm telling you.

330
00:16:05.565 --> 00:16:07.876
It's there. It's right there.
It's subtle. but it's right there.

331
00:16:07.900 --> 00:16:09.140
Well. what is it? I don't know.

332
00:16:09.202 --> 00:16:10.245
It's nothing we manufacture.

333
00:16:10.269 --> 00:16:11.380
Aren't you supposed to
know this kind of stuff?

334
00:16:11.404 --> 00:16:13.382
Shawn. I sell pharmaceutical
supplies. I'm not a scientist!

335
00:16:13.406 --> 00:16:16.103
But you're saying it is
something? Yes. I'm pretty sure.

336
00:16:19.078 --> 00:16:20.171
Don't eat it!

337
00:16:20.246 --> 00:16:21.976
What. do I look like an idiot?

338
00:16:28.688 --> 00:16:30.328
What... What... Are
you taking some to go?

339
00:16:30.356 --> 00:16:32.916
Yes! For the road! In case
later on I get hungry enough

340
00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:34.552
to eat something that
might be poisoned!

341
00:16:38.064 --> 00:16:40.590
There are four up there.
and two on the other side.

342
00:16:41.501 --> 00:16:42.578
What. you mean those
two guys up there?

343
00:16:42.602 --> 00:16:45.367
Excuse me. hi. it's time.
The press are ready.

344
00:16:45.438 --> 00:16:46.531
Thank you. All right.

345
00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:49.668
Man. we gotta go!

346
00:16:51.711 --> 00:16:52.988
Sorry. could I
just try that again?

347
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:55.311
I kind of fumbled the
"safe and secure" part.

348
00:16:55.381 --> 00:16:56.542
Sure.

349
00:16:56.749 --> 00:16:57.808
Be sensitive.

350
00:16:57.884 --> 00:16:58.977
Of course.

351
00:16:59.051 --> 00:17:01.543
The finals will continue
tomorrow as scheduled.

352
00:17:01.621 --> 00:17:05.149
At this point. all indications are
Mr. Cavanaugh was having a heart attack.

353
00:17:05.224 --> 00:17:07.921
stumbled forward. falling
over the railing to his death.

354
00:17:08.160 --> 00:17:09.753
But we wanna assure everyone

355
00:17:09.829 --> 00:17:11.491
that this building
is both safe and...

356
00:17:11.564 --> 00:17:13.829
Our sympathies go out
to Mr. Cavanaugh's family.

357
00:17:13.900 --> 00:17:15.425
and we would like
to offer counseling

358
00:17:15.501 --> 00:17:17.746
to anyone who feels that they might
need it. SHAWN: Who's the blonde?

359
00:17:17.770 --> 00:17:19.948
Lassiter's new partner.
They transferred his girlfriend.

360
00:17:19.972 --> 00:17:23.670
And again. we wanna ensure everyone
coming out for this fantastic event

361
00:17:23.743 --> 00:17:25.234
that it is entirely safe.

362
00:17:25.311 --> 00:17:26.588
Shawn! They're gonna
stop investigating!

363
00:17:26.612 --> 00:17:28.724
One last question. and then I
really have to go wrap up this thing.

364
00:17:28.748 --> 00:17:29.748
Do something!

365
00:17:29.815 --> 00:17:32.227
Is there any word as to what
Cavanaugh's big announcement was?

366
00:17:32.251 --> 00:17:33.879
Moo goo gai pan!

367
00:17:34.453 --> 00:17:36.786
Beef lo mein. kung pao!

368
00:17:38.424 --> 00:17:41.326
Check the food! It was murder!

369
00:17:42.361 --> 00:17:45.388
Oh. did I just say
all that out loud?

370
00:17:47.934 --> 00:17:50.134
Shawn. you'll never find
out what that is without a lab.

371
00:17:50.202 --> 00:17:51.135
I'll get a lab.

372
00:17:51.203 --> 00:17:52.899
A high-tech lab? Right now?

373
00:17:52.972 --> 00:17:53.996
Maybe.

374
00:17:55.007 --> 00:17:56.908
Might have a connection.

375
00:17:57.877 --> 00:17:58.877
Yo!

376
00:17:59.645 --> 00:18:01.705
Shawn. Hey. Dad. great shirt!

377
00:18:02.882 --> 00:18:04.043
You want something.

378
00:18:04.116 --> 00:18:05.394
Why do you always
think I want something?

379
00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:08.855
Oh. you don't want anything.
What a pleasant surprise.

380
00:18:10.156 --> 00:18:12.455
Okay. you got me!
I want something.

381
00:18:12.525 --> 00:18:14.460
I got a poker
game in 45 minutes.

382
00:18:14.527 --> 00:18:16.086
You still talk to Jim Syklan?

383
00:18:16.162 --> 00:18:18.358
Syklan? Sometimes.
Why. what's he to you?

384
00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:20.309
Is he still working at the
regional crime lab out here?

385
00:18:20.333 --> 00:18:21.562
Last I checked. Why?

386
00:18:21.634 --> 00:18:23.796
I need to know what this is.

387
00:18:24.971 --> 00:18:27.167
It looks like a Number
15 with chicken.

388
00:18:27.873 --> 00:18:29.671
Dad. you made a joke!

389
00:18:30.142 --> 00:18:32.338
I think there's poison in it.

390
00:18:33.446 --> 00:18:34.937
Goodbye. Shawn.

391
00:18:35.314 --> 00:18:36.314
(GROANS)

392
00:18:37.817 --> 00:18:39.809
It's just one time! Once!

393
00:18:39.885 --> 00:18:42.946
No cases. Shawn! I was
painfully clear about that.

394
00:18:43.022 --> 00:18:44.923
Oh. no. no. this
isn't for a case.

395
00:18:44.991 --> 00:18:47.017
This is for a friend.

396
00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:50.555
Oh. friend. different.

397
00:18:51.597 --> 00:18:52.597
No!

398
00:18:57.269 --> 00:19:00.262
Look. I'll do anything.
whatever you want. it's one favor.

399
00:19:00.339 --> 00:19:04.037
Anything he can tell me about this
would be very helpful. it's serious.

400
00:19:04.110 --> 00:19:05.908
Shawn. this is really
important to you?

401
00:19:05.978 --> 00:19:07.037
Extremely.

402
00:19:07.113 --> 00:19:08.342
And you'll do anything?

403
00:19:08.414 --> 00:19:09.712
Name it.

404
00:19:10.850 --> 00:19:12.148
(CHUCKLING)

405
00:19:12.685 --> 00:19:13.685
Grab a saw.

406
00:19:14.587 --> 00:19:15.611
What. now?

407
00:19:15.688 --> 00:19:18.283
Well. you said you'd
do anything. right?

408
00:19:20.526 --> 00:19:25.521
You know. most people will wait five. six
whole minutes before they cash in a favor.

409
00:19:26.565 --> 00:19:28.158
I will not saw
through bone for you.

410
00:19:28.234 --> 00:19:29.566
(CHUCKLING)

411
00:19:34.974 --> 00:19:37.967
The doghouse? From eighth grade?

412
00:19:38.310 --> 00:19:40.677
Well. it's not
really a doghouse.

413
00:19:41.414 --> 00:19:42.507
Not yet.

414
00:19:42.581 --> 00:19:43.981
What do you want me to do?

415
00:19:44.050 --> 00:19:45.074
Finish it.

416
00:19:45.151 --> 00:19:46.449
What. now?

417
00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:49.648
Or whenever you
want your information.

418
00:19:49.722 --> 00:19:53.989
You got more wood out back. nails on
the workbench. Home Depot's open till 9:00.

419
00:19:54.060 --> 00:19:55.926
Don't cut any corners.

420
00:20:00.166 --> 00:20:01.691
You're insane!

421
00:20:01.867 --> 00:20:03.233
You're losing light.

422
00:20:04.603 --> 00:20:06.469
Make sure you lock up.

423
00:20:11.043 --> 00:20:13.274
It's creepy that you kept this!

424
00:20:18.784 --> 00:20:21.151
(DOG BARKING) Shawn.
you've done absolutely nothing

425
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:23.780
to convince me that you're
responsible enough for a dog.

426
00:20:23.856 --> 00:20:24.966
You'll never give me a chance.

427
00:20:24.990 --> 00:20:26.982
Chances are earned. Shawn.

428
00:20:27.059 --> 00:20:29.187
You'll never let me earn it!

429
00:20:32.965 --> 00:20:34.365
Fair enough.

430
00:20:35.334 --> 00:20:36.927
You're gonna need a doghouse.

431
00:20:37.002 --> 00:20:39.494
I saw one at the hardware
store. No. No. no. no.

432
00:20:39.572 --> 00:20:42.064
You're gonna make it. I can't.

433
00:20:42.141 --> 00:20:43.518
Well. it seems to me
that somebody who thinks

434
00:20:43.542 --> 00:20:45.909
they're responsible enough
for the life of an animal

435
00:20:45.978 --> 00:20:50.939
should certainly be able to construct
a roof for the ratty little thing.

436
00:20:51.150 --> 00:20:54.177
All right. I'll make it.
I'll make it right now.

437
00:21:05.698 --> 00:21:07.166
What is that?

438
00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:11.170
"What is that?" It's the
doghouse. No. it's not.

439
00:21:11.237 --> 00:21:12.466
What are you talking about?

440
00:21:12.538 --> 00:21:14.336
I gave you specifications.

441
00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:17.105
When? When I gave you the job.

442
00:21:18.744 --> 00:21:20.076
In 1989?

443
00:21:20.146 --> 00:21:23.810
Shawn. you know as well as I
do this is not what I asked for.

444
00:21:24.817 --> 00:21:27.218
Keep working. Don't be too loud.

445
00:21:27.753 --> 00:21:29.949
The neighbors
are trying to sleep.

446
00:21:31.624 --> 00:21:32.785
(DOOR OPENS)

447
00:21:34.293 --> 00:21:35.386
(DOOR CLOSES)

448
00:22:04.623 --> 00:22:05.682
(CHUCKLES)

449
00:22:05.758 --> 00:22:07.283
You expect me to
be okay with this?

450
00:22:07.359 --> 00:22:08.383
I worked hard on it.

451
00:22:08.460 --> 00:22:10.292
Shawn. you've been
at this for hours now.

452
00:22:10.362 --> 00:22:11.907
The nails aren't
pounded in all the way.

453
00:22:11.931 --> 00:22:13.441
the base has gotta
be up off the ground.

454
00:22:13.465 --> 00:22:15.559
If it rains. the rain's
gonna flow right in.

455
00:22:15.634 --> 00:22:16.978
And who's gonna fit
in through that door?

456
00:22:17.002 --> 00:22:18.402
That door's not high enough.

457
00:22:18.470 --> 00:22:20.769
I built it. Dad. what
do you want me to do?

458
00:22:20.840 --> 00:22:22.706
I want you to do it right.

459
00:22:34.520 --> 00:22:35.886
(TIRES SCREECHING)

460
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:41.918
(SHAWN GRUNTING)

461
00:22:48.868 --> 00:22:52.464
Listen. Dr. Sloane. if I can get
you this product this afternoon.

462
00:22:52.538 --> 00:22:56.236
would it be possible to sit
down with you to discuss the...

463
00:22:57.710 --> 00:23:00.111
<i>M-A...</i>

464
00:23:00.946 --> 00:23:04.348
The unbelievable results
we've been having...

465
00:23:07.753 --> 00:23:09.119
<i>0...</i>

466
00:23:09.188 --> 00:23:11.282
I'm sorry. Can I call you back?

467
00:23:12.391 --> 00:23:13.586
Thanks.

468
00:23:18.831 --> 00:23:20.197
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

469
00:23:21.267 --> 00:23:23.668
Burton Guster. Shawn?

470
00:23:24.737 --> 00:23:26.569
You're in the hospital?

471
00:23:27.273 --> 00:23:28.400
What happened?

472
00:23:28.774 --> 00:23:30.037
(GROANING) You call your dad?

473
00:23:30.109 --> 00:23:32.078
I'm fine. They're releasing me.

474
00:23:32.144 --> 00:23:33.612
Did you call him?

475
00:23:34.613 --> 00:23:36.707
Gus. I am not
gonna talk to my dad.

476
00:23:36.782 --> 00:23:38.546
He'd wanna know you're okay.

477
00:23:38.617 --> 00:23:40.813
All he cares about are results.

478
00:23:40.886 --> 00:23:43.879
Just like those possessed
spelling bee parents.

479
00:23:44.456 --> 00:23:47.085
You know what's wrong
with this? All of this.

480
00:23:47.293 --> 00:23:49.285
Shawn. you're
delirious. You're upset.

481
00:23:49.361 --> 00:23:51.762
You lost control of
your bike last night.

482
00:23:53.098 --> 00:23:54.623
Gus. I didn't lose
control of anything.

483
00:23:54.700 --> 00:23:58.159
Someone tried to kill me or
send a very serious message.

484
00:24:01.173 --> 00:24:02.903
Brendan appreciates
you checking on him.

485
00:24:02.975 --> 00:24:04.252
Well. we were in
the neighborhood.

486
00:24:04.276 --> 00:24:06.507
And. Gus here is a huge fan.

487
00:24:06.845 --> 00:24:09.474
He almost won the
spelling bee himself.

488
00:24:09.949 --> 00:24:11.850
I took some bad advice.

489
00:24:17.289 --> 00:24:19.315
Well. Brendan's
going home tomorrow.

490
00:24:19.391 --> 00:24:20.791
He's fine.

491
00:24:20.859 --> 00:24:23.488
He's more upset about
missing the spelling bee.

492
00:24:24.196 --> 00:24:27.360
Well. maybe they'll decide
to redo the whole thing.

493
00:24:28.233 --> 00:24:29.826
Why'd they do that?

494
00:24:32.204 --> 00:24:33.763
Did you see the inhaler?

495
00:24:33.839 --> 00:24:35.330
Same one as that
little Czech kid?

496
00:24:35.407 --> 00:24:36.431
Get me a seating chart.

497
00:24:36.508 --> 00:24:38.853
I'll bet you I know who Brendan
was sitting next to on day one.

498
00:24:38.877 --> 00:24:40.345
I already checked it out. Nice!

499
00:24:40.412 --> 00:24:43.109
Shawn. something's going
on with that Czech kid.

500
00:24:43.182 --> 00:24:46.084
Talk to me. The doctor on his
inhaler. Dr. Zavin. in Ventura?

501
00:24:46.151 --> 00:24:47.642
Yeah? He doesn't exist.

502
00:24:47.720 --> 00:24:50.952
I do training on that route. The last
doctor in the book is Youngerman.

503
00:24:51.023 --> 00:24:52.548
I double-checked it today.

504
00:24:52.624 --> 00:24:54.820
You're saying that inhaler...

505
00:24:54.893 --> 00:24:56.225
Is a fake.

506
00:24:56.495 --> 00:24:57.929
(LAUGHING)

507
00:24:58.764 --> 00:24:59.788
Where you going?

508
00:24:59.865 --> 00:25:03.393
I am going to build a doghouse!

509
00:25:10.142 --> 00:25:11.940
I thought you gave up.

510
00:25:12.177 --> 00:25:14.772
Yeah. well. it doesn't
appear so. huh?

511
00:25:16.215 --> 00:25:17.255
What happened to your leg?

512
00:25:17.282 --> 00:25:19.012
Absolutely nothing.

513
00:25:19.251 --> 00:25:22.221
You're running your
roofing vertical there. huh?

514
00:25:22.287 --> 00:25:23.287
Yeah.

515
00:25:24.056 --> 00:25:26.355
You might wanna pop
a ridge beam in first.

516
00:25:26.425 --> 00:25:29.725
Well. yeah. that's a given.

517
00:25:42.908 --> 00:25:44.240
What the hell are you doing?

518
00:25:44.309 --> 00:25:45.971
I'm gonna help you.

519
00:25:46.545 --> 00:25:48.571
You've never helped
me before. ever.

520
00:25:48.647 --> 00:25:50.240
You've never asked.

521
00:25:51.517 --> 00:25:53.042
Put a nail in here.

522
00:25:56.488 --> 00:25:59.151
All right. This is weird.

523
00:26:06.565 --> 00:26:07.760
No. thanks.

524
00:26:18.210 --> 00:26:19.337
Not bad.

525
00:26:19.411 --> 00:26:20.411
(SCOFFS)

526
00:26:20.479 --> 00:26:21.845
"Not bad"?

527
00:26:21.914 --> 00:26:23.906
It's like the Park
Hyatt for poodles.

528
00:26:23.982 --> 00:26:26.008
Will you call Jack Syklan?

529
00:26:26.952 --> 00:26:28.921
What is this? Your results.

530
00:26:28.987 --> 00:26:30.785
We had an agreement.

531
00:26:31.423 --> 00:26:33.915
This is a derivative of methyl
parathion. High-grade stuff.

532
00:26:33.992 --> 00:26:36.826
Whatever you're into. I
want you to get out quick.

533
00:26:36.895 --> 00:26:38.557
I'm not kidding.

534
00:26:42.734 --> 00:26:45.329
Wait a sec. How did
you get this so quickly?

535
00:26:45.404 --> 00:26:48.203
Hmm? Oh. Syklan's a
part of my poker game.

536
00:26:49.007 --> 00:26:51.238
So you didn't even
have to call him?

537
00:26:51.310 --> 00:26:53.404
That game was at his house.

538
00:26:54.012 --> 00:26:56.607
And I did all of
that for nothing?

539
00:26:56.949 --> 00:27:00.351
For nothing? Shawn. you've
never completed a thing in your life.

540
00:27:03.222 --> 00:27:04.656
Now you have.

541
00:27:14.867 --> 00:27:15.960
Poisoned?

542
00:27:16.034 --> 00:27:18.503
I feel somebody
poisoned his food.

543
00:27:18.570 --> 00:27:20.061
There is a

544
00:27:21.473 --> 00:27:24.773
Styrofoam container.
yes. and a...

545
00:27:25.611 --> 00:27:27.136
(GROANING)

546
00:27:28.981 --> 00:27:31.416
"Happiness is a
golden poem." What?

547
00:27:31.950 --> 00:27:33.328
(IMITATES CRACKING)
A fortune cookie!

548
00:27:33.352 --> 00:27:34.581
This is ridiculous. Is it?

549
00:27:34.653 --> 00:27:38.715
Mr. Spencer. what we have now
points to a medical condition. not murder.

550
00:27:38.790 --> 00:27:41.885
All appearances show Mr. Cavanaugh
having an anaphylactic reaction.

551
00:27:41.960 --> 00:27:45.920
Not to be out of line. but that could be
triggered by several types of poisons.

552
00:27:45.998 --> 00:27:47.125
Or altered medications.

553
00:27:47.199 --> 00:27:48.895
Or shellfish. which
he was allergic to.

554
00:27:48.967 --> 00:27:51.869
Those results will show
up in the toxicology report.

555
00:27:51.937 --> 00:27:54.015
which we will have a copy of
in approximately two weeks.

556
00:27:54.039 --> 00:27:55.564
No. no. no! That'll be too late.

557
00:27:55.641 --> 00:27:57.633
All the contestants
will be gone...

558
00:27:59.178 --> 00:28:00.271
Home.

559
00:28:01.180 --> 00:28:04.048
You won't be able to
finish a real investigation.

560
00:28:04.116 --> 00:28:06.711
Chief. I sense this!

561
00:28:07.186 --> 00:28:08.363
Look. something
got out of control

562
00:28:08.387 --> 00:28:10.879
and the perpetrator was
willing to kill to cover it up!

563
00:28:10.956 --> 00:28:12.857
What proof do you have?

564
00:28:20.599 --> 00:28:22.227
Only what I feel.

565
00:28:22.901 --> 00:28:24.312
Why are you still
listening to this crap?

566
00:28:24.336 --> 00:28:25.599
Dude. what is your glitch?

567
00:28:25.671 --> 00:28:27.640
You! You're my glitch!

568
00:28:27.706 --> 00:28:29.651
Look. he got nowhere with
his little inhaler assignment.

569
00:28:29.675 --> 00:28:31.974
and then he tells the media
that we had a murder scene!

570
00:28:32.044 --> 00:28:33.842
Cut him loose. Karen!

571
00:28:38.016 --> 00:28:41.680
I mean. do whatever
you think is best. Chief.

572
00:28:42.821 --> 00:28:45.620
Mr. Cavanaugh was gonna make
an announcement. What about that?

573
00:28:45.691 --> 00:28:47.502
The Director said he'd
recently spoken of retiring.

574
00:28:47.526 --> 00:28:48.736
That's not what
he was gonna say.

575
00:28:48.760 --> 00:28:50.058
Oh. you know?

576
00:28:50.128 --> 00:28:51.152
I know.

577
00:28:51.230 --> 00:28:54.689
Mr. Spencer. I asked you to
check in about the inhaler incident.

578
00:28:54.766 --> 00:28:56.211
If you or your partner
have anything about that.

579
00:28:56.235 --> 00:28:58.204
I'd be happy to hear about it.

580
00:28:58.270 --> 00:28:59.499
Otherwise...

581
00:29:07.446 --> 00:29:09.438
We gotta get back into
the spellmaster's room.

582
00:29:09.514 --> 00:29:10.959
Are you serious? Gus.
the killer was there!

583
00:29:10.983 --> 00:29:13.851
There's gotta be some
other piece of evidence inside.

584
00:29:14.186 --> 00:29:16.655
We're not gonna have
time to get in there.

585
00:29:16.722 --> 00:29:17.917
Besides. it's locked.

586
00:29:17.990 --> 00:29:19.322
We'll make it work.

587
00:29:20.192 --> 00:29:21.592
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

588
00:29:21.860 --> 00:29:24.056
How hard is it to get into
this event without a ticket?

589
00:29:24.129 --> 00:29:25.529
Impossible.

590
00:29:26.498 --> 00:29:29.263
The new spellmaster.
Check it out.

591
00:29:30.168 --> 00:29:32.660
It's exactly what I
was hoping you'd say.

592
00:29:36.341 --> 00:29:37.434
You can't do that to him!

593
00:29:37.509 --> 00:29:41.071
Gus. he has to learn sometime
that smoking is bad for him.

594
00:29:43.915 --> 00:29:45.941
We're picking it up as a
new round commences.

595
00:29:46.018 --> 00:29:47.495
A lot of excitement
in the air. Ooh. yeah.

596
00:29:47.519 --> 00:29:49.681
The tension is becoming
butyraceous. Bud.

597
00:29:57.162 --> 00:29:58.425
(GROANS)

598
00:29:59.665 --> 00:30:02.760
I'm so sorry if my agonizing
pain is inconveniencing you.

599
00:30:10.976 --> 00:30:12.376
What's this?

600
00:30:13.578 --> 00:30:15.979
It's a mark on a
carpet. Let's go.

601
00:30:16.315 --> 00:30:18.045
Someone must have heard that.

602
00:30:18.116 --> 00:30:20.950
<i>MAN: Thirty seconds.
Live to air. Positions. please.</i>

603
00:30:21.019 --> 00:30:22.351
Time's up. Shawn.

604
00:30:22.421 --> 00:30:23.548
(GRUNTS)

605
00:30:23.789 --> 00:30:25.724
Did you hear me. Shawn?

606
00:30:28.493 --> 00:30:29.984
I've got something!

607
00:30:34.900 --> 00:30:35.900
Yes!

608
00:30:37.703 --> 00:30:39.672
<i>Ten seconds.
Prepare the next word.</i>

609
00:30:40.072 --> 00:30:41.131
That can't be right.

610
00:30:41.206 --> 00:30:42.717
It doesn't mean
anything. Shawn. let's go.

611
00:30:42.741 --> 00:30:47.304
<i>Broadcast in five.
four. three. two...</i>

612
00:30:48.013 --> 00:30:49.413
Maybe this direction.

613
00:30:49.481 --> 00:30:51.643
<i>Hello? We need the word now.</i>

614
00:30:52.851 --> 00:30:54.615
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

615
00:30:56.121 --> 00:30:58.556
<i>Leann. something's
wrong. send security.</i>

616
00:31:00.392 --> 00:31:02.623
No. sorry for the delay.

617
00:31:03.428 --> 00:31:04.589
Give me a word! A word?

618
00:31:04.663 --> 00:31:06.341
Yeah! Something hard.
but something you can spell.

619
00:31:06.365 --> 00:31:09.164
I can spell anything.
Except "aggiornamento."

620
00:31:09.901 --> 00:31:10.925
Give me one! No!

621
00:31:11.002 --> 00:31:12.080
You are not gonna
be spellmaster!

622
00:31:12.104 --> 00:31:14.938
Gus. give me a word so we can
get out of here! We're so close!

623
00:31:15.907 --> 00:31:18.001
<i>Is everything okay up there?</i>

624
00:31:19.277 --> 00:31:20.609
It's fine.

625
00:31:21.980 --> 00:31:23.243
"Banana."

626
00:31:27.185 --> 00:31:28.710
<i>Can you repeat that?</i>

627
00:31:29.388 --> 00:31:30.481
<i>Yes.</i>

628
00:31:31.390 --> 00:31:32.756
<i>"Banana."</i>

629
00:31:34.226 --> 00:31:36.092
"Banana." Shawn?
This is the third round!

630
00:31:36.161 --> 00:31:37.220
You could have helped me!

631
00:31:37.295 --> 00:31:39.628
This is a dead end. Shawn.
we're walking. Let's go!

632
00:31:39.698 --> 00:31:41.530
<i>Definition. please?</i>

633
00:31:42.100 --> 00:31:43.227
What?

634
00:31:45.871 --> 00:31:46.871
(FEEDBACK)

635
00:31:46.938 --> 00:31:48.372
<i>A yellow fruit.</i>

636
00:31:48.974 --> 00:31:51.068
<i>Also. a kind of pudding.</i>

637
00:31:51.877 --> 00:31:53.675
<i>A delicious pudding.</i>

638
00:31:54.146 --> 00:31:55.580
<i>Sentence. please?</i>

639
00:31:59.117 --> 00:32:03.817
<i>"Anna Banana would like to
hear</i> Venus <i>by Bananarama."</i>

640
00:32:04.322 --> 00:32:05.585
<i>"Banana."</i>

641
00:32:05.657 --> 00:32:08.684
<i>B-A-N-A-N-A. Banana.</i>

642
00:32:08.760 --> 00:32:10.319
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)

643
00:32:14.466 --> 00:32:16.935
Oh. wait a second.
I've got something!

644
00:32:18.103 --> 00:32:20.265
Dude. we got him! He
was watching the Czech.

645
00:32:20.338 --> 00:32:21.533
Let me see.

646
00:32:21.606 --> 00:32:23.734
<i>We need to get the next word.</i>

647
00:32:24.843 --> 00:32:26.277
Give me a word. No!

648
00:32:26.344 --> 00:32:27.455
You're ruining the whole event!

649
00:32:27.479 --> 00:32:28.970
Suit yourself.

650
00:32:29.714 --> 00:32:30.909
<i>"Onion."</i>

651
00:32:31.616 --> 00:32:32.845
"Onion?"

652
00:32:33.518 --> 00:32:34.679
<i>"Onion?"</i>

653
00:32:34.753 --> 00:32:35.948
"Onion?"

654
00:32:36.254 --> 00:32:38.485
Even Dan Quayle
could spell that.

655
00:32:38.557 --> 00:32:40.492
<i>O-N-I-O-N. Onion.</i>

656
00:32:41.560 --> 00:32:43.222
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

657
00:32:45.997 --> 00:32:47.727
<i>Are we off the list. Bill?</i>

658
00:32:47.799 --> 00:32:49.665
No. everything's fine.

659
00:32:50.702 --> 00:32:52.000
You're using his grocery list!

660
00:32:52.070 --> 00:32:53.936
You refused to help me!

661
00:32:54.005 --> 00:32:56.236
Now I gotta give
them something else.

662
00:32:58.076 --> 00:32:59.476
<i>"Mitchum."</i>

663
00:32:59.911 --> 00:33:01.345
(ALL LAUGHING)

664
00:33:03.448 --> 00:33:05.280
<i>"Mitchum"? Yes.</i>

665
00:33:05.817 --> 00:33:10.983
<i>"When I go to Albertsons. I need
to buy some Mitchum Ice Blast."</i>

666
00:33:14.092 --> 00:33:16.061
<i>"And bananas."</i>

667
00:33:16.795 --> 00:33:19.629
That wasn't me! I
was locked outside.

668
00:33:19.798 --> 00:33:21.994
I have a reputation to uphold!

669
00:33:24.736 --> 00:33:27.137
So he was watching the
Czech. we have no proof.

670
00:33:27.205 --> 00:33:28.867
There was no film in the camera!

671
00:33:28.940 --> 00:33:32.502
He was using that lens for something
else besides taking pictures. Now. what?

672
00:33:32.577 --> 00:33:34.422
Cavanaugh was known for
ferreting out rule breakers.

673
00:33:34.446 --> 00:33:36.486
He once caught a kid
stealing the advance word list.

674
00:33:36.548 --> 00:33:38.710
And everything he
did had a purpose.

675
00:33:48.426 --> 00:33:51.225
You couldn't have grabbed
one of these five minute ago?

676
00:33:55.066 --> 00:33:57.365
<i>MAN: We're down to
the final two spellers.</i>

677
00:33:57.435 --> 00:34:00.303
<i>This has been a hard-fought
battle right from the start!</i>

678
00:34:00.372 --> 00:34:02.534
<i>We've had tragedy. controversy.</i>

679
00:34:02.607 --> 00:34:06.169
<i>but when it really mattered. these
kids put together a fantastic display</i>

680
00:34:06.244 --> 00:34:07.576
<i>of the power of learning.</i>

681
00:34:07.646 --> 00:34:08.909
(SCOFFS)

682
00:34:08.980 --> 00:34:12.348
Look at this. Brendan Vu
went down on "gladiolus."

683
00:34:13.018 --> 00:34:14.042
So?

684
00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:17.956
So? If I'd been able to see any of
the competition. I could have told you

685
00:34:18.023 --> 00:34:21.653
that was the winning word
from the first spelling bee in 1929.

686
00:34:21.760 --> 00:34:23.820
Okay. you're scaring me again.

687
00:34:24.629 --> 00:34:27.861
All of these words from that
round were the winning words.

688
00:34:28.033 --> 00:34:31.197
They do that once in a while.
they make it a theme round.

689
00:34:31.269 --> 00:34:33.363
This one won the 1985 bee.

690
00:34:34.472 --> 00:34:35.997
this one from 1943.

691
00:34:36.074 --> 00:34:37.906
Gus. what are you saying?

692
00:34:38.710 --> 00:34:41.839
Guess which kid got the
winning word from 1953?

693
00:34:43.982 --> 00:34:46.008
You're staring at his father.

694
00:34:50.889 --> 00:34:53.358
Gus. that's who Cavanaugh
was gonna disqualify.

695
00:34:53.425 --> 00:34:55.326
That's what he was
tracking in the rulebook!

696
00:34:55.393 --> 00:34:56.952
1953! It was 1953.

697
00:34:57.028 --> 00:34:59.657
<i>FINEMAN: Jiri Prochazka.
you have the next word.</i>

698
00:34:59.898 --> 00:35:01.457
<i>"Mastoparietal."</i>

699
00:35:03.368 --> 00:35:05.064
<i>Part of speech?</i>

700
00:35:05.136 --> 00:35:06.900
<i>It is an adjective.</i>

701
00:35:07.706 --> 00:35:09.834
<i>(STAMMERING) Could
I have the definition?</i>

702
00:35:09.908 --> 00:35:11.035
<i>Yes.</i>

703
00:35:11.109 --> 00:35:14.637
<i>"Relating to the mastoid
portion of the temporal bone.</i>

704
00:35:14.713 --> 00:35:16.443
<i>"and to the parietal lobe."</i>

705
00:35:23.655 --> 00:35:24.782
<i>M...</i>

706
00:35:25.957 --> 00:35:30.224
<i>A-S-T...</i>

707
00:35:31.896 --> 00:35:37.665
<i>O-P-A-R-I...</i>

708
00:35:38.703 --> 00:35:40.865
I got him. Let's call the Chief.

709
00:35:40.939 --> 00:35:46.139
<i>And this year's winner of the
Central California Regionals</i>

710
00:35:46.211 --> 00:35:48.806
<i>is Jiri Prochazka!</i>

711
00:35:53.385 --> 00:35:54.944
(SHAWN WHOOPING)

712
00:35:57.856 --> 00:36:01.156
Move out. people. this is what
you came to see. right here.

713
00:36:01.226 --> 00:36:02.854
This is it! Yes!

714
00:36:04.696 --> 00:36:07.188
This competition meant
everything to Miklous!

715
00:36:09.267 --> 00:36:12.567
Oh. boy! Gus! Gus. here we go!

716
00:36:12.637 --> 00:36:14.230
Gus. it's happening!

717
00:36:14.305 --> 00:36:15.603
(GROANING)

718
00:36:23.748 --> 00:36:26.149
I know who killed
Elvin Cavanaugh.

719
00:36:26.885 --> 00:36:29.548
Can't he ever just tell
us to arrest someone?

720
00:36:29.621 --> 00:36:30.919
He does this a lot?

721
00:36:30.989 --> 00:36:32.013
BOTH: Yes.

722
00:36:32.090 --> 00:36:36.460
I'm sorry. I'm kind of a slave
to my visions. I'm a slave.

723
00:36:36.795 --> 00:36:37.922
Do you want me to cuff him?

724
00:36:37.996 --> 00:36:39.862
Why would I want that?

725
00:36:40.598 --> 00:36:42.260
Just a suggestion.

726
00:36:42.667 --> 00:36:45.637
They just sort of come
when they wanna come. and...

727
00:36:45.904 --> 00:36:47.031
Jiri.

728
00:36:49.808 --> 00:36:51.367
Spell "soubrette."

729
00:36:52.711 --> 00:36:54.179
Why is this man speaking?

730
00:36:54.245 --> 00:36:55.873
You can't. can you?

731
00:36:55.947 --> 00:36:58.178
Not without help from your dad.

732
00:36:59.184 --> 00:37:01.676
And that's not a
real inhaler. is it?

733
00:37:01.753 --> 00:37:03.915
This is crazy. this... This...

734
00:37:09.127 --> 00:37:11.926
<i>SHAWN: Cheating was
Cavanaugh's obsession.</i>

735
00:37:12.397 --> 00:37:15.231
He was gonna expose
you as a cheater.

736
00:37:15.300 --> 00:37:17.235
He was gonna disqualify
Jiri. and you knew it.

737
00:37:17.302 --> 00:37:18.895
and you couldn't
let that happen.

738
